Defendant Clinton J Kramer in court with attorney Timothy T. Kay.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a no contest plea to Counts1, 2 and 3 of the amended information.  Court finds defendant guilty.  The victim's mother addresses the Court.      The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS JAIL (CREDIT - 8 days if revoked);

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling;
*Contact allowed with D.M.T. and family as deemed appropriate by agent;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Mental Heath/psychologocial evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.
*Attend Anger Management.
*Attend Parenting Class.
*Perform 50 hours community service.
*Write Letter of apology to victim.
*Any other conditions deemed appropriate by agent.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (apply cash bail);

Count #2:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS JAIL (consecutive to count #1);

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
same as count 1.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (apply cash bail);

Count #3:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS JAIL (consecutive to counts #1 and #2);

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
same as count 1 & 2.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
